               <scopecontent id="aspace_913a7c99c4e8141b0ebb5cada9510b13">
                  <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                  <p>This is a sheet with several ink and pencil sketches by Igor Filipchenko for the bookplate of Ėrast Pavlovich Garin (1902-1980), who was a comic actor in Soviet film and theater. Also included are the resulting bookplate (signed by the artist in pencil) and a 1983 Russian newspaper clipping about how films and actors inspire ex-libris designs (according to bookseller's description).</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c>
            <c id="ref45" level="item">
               <did>
                  <unittitle>Design for the bookplate of the Memorial Museum.</unittitle>
                  <unitdate unitdatetype="inclusive">undated</unitdate>
                  <physdesc id="aspace_f0ceeb3a4d7ad46ae26c8dd2b24c9b6f">2 drawings on 1 sheet : ink ; 12.4 x 15.3 cm</physdesc>
                  <physdesc id="aspace_57090749e1e145cea405be18527ae371">1 bookplate ; 8.8 x 6.9 cm</physdesc>
                  <physdesc id="aspace_6e7dce448a81c20de8c7208b10d117d6">1 newspaper clipping</physdesc>
                  <container containerid="39002075066564"
                             id="aspace_5a39485a7e6a01235abbabcf5bf2b78e"
                             label="Mixed Materials"
                             localtype="box">1</container>
               </did>
               <custodhist id="aspace_d674a1cc9abd05f10db8bb0de4f78193">
