               </custodhist>
               <scopecontent id="aspace_3048f7056bbbe8124e7a240c0f81d1c1">
                  <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                  <p>This is a sheet with two drawings in ink by Igor Filipchenko for the bookplate of the Memorial Museum. The design depicts Basil (Vasilii Vasil'evich) Porik (1920-1944), a lieutenant in the Soviet Army who was active in the resistance movement in France during World War II and later named a hero of the Soviet Union. Also included are the resulting bookplate (with the artist's stamp on the verso) and a 1985 Russian newspaper clipping about an ex-libris exhibition held at Bookshop No. 14 in Vinnytsya, Ukraine, and dedicated to the 40th anniversary of the Great Patriotic War (according to bookseller's description).</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c>
            <c id="ref51" level="item">
               <did>
                  <unittitle>Design for the bookplate of Ranier M. Rilke.</unittitle>
                  <unitdate unitdatetype="inclusive">undated</unitdate>
