               </custodhist>
               <scopecontent id="aspace_e7ab2a3eda43da76fc584f6676afa180">
                  <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                  <p>This design is an example of an "imaginary bookplate." Rather than referring to mythical or fantastic subject matter, an imaginary bookplate is an artist's conception of a personal ex-libris design without consent or even contact with the designated patron. Artists often create imaginary bookplates for famous individuals, such as writers, politicians, celebrities, etc.</p>
                  <p>Artist's monogram possibly H. J.</p>
               </scopecontent>
            </c>
